In England, in the seven days to 03 March, there were 186,929 new confirmed cases (330.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 February, there were 187,935 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 1% (1,006 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 08 March is 16,321,911 (28,862.7 cases per 100,000 population).
